0a-d6c5-4425-96b8-9c47a378a3bd\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/add-copilot-agent\",\"slug\":\"buzzing-tinkering-coral\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01LV8AeSWFZZTG1WQEdb9dMB\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Perfect! Now let me create a comprehensive summary of the findings:\\n\\n## Agent Integration Pattern Analysis\\n\\nI've thoroughly examined the existing agent integration patterns in the codebase. Here are all the findings organized by topic:\\n\\n### 1. **Registry Keys and Constants** (`cmd/entire/cli/agent/registry.go`)\\n\\nAgent names are registered with **lowercase-with-hyphens** registry keys:\\n\\n```go\\nconst (\\n    AgentNameClaudeCode types.AgentName = \\\"claude-code\\\"\\n    AgentNameCursor     types.AgentName = \\\"cursor\\\"\\n    AgentNameGemini     types.AgentName = \\\"gemini\\\"\\n    AgentNameOpenCode   types.AgentName = \\\"opencode\\\"\\n)\\n\\nconst (\\n    AgentTypeClaudeCode types.AgentType = \\\"Claude Code\\\"\\n    AgentTypeCursor     types.AgentType = \\\"Cursor\\\"\\n    AgentTypeGemini     types.AgentType = \\\"Gemini CLI\\\"\\n    AgentTypeOpenCode   types.AgentType = \\\"OpenCode\\\"\\n)\\n```\\n\\n**Key observations:**\\n- `AgentName` is the **registry key** used in CLI commands and code (lowercase-hyphenated: `\\\"claude-code\\\"`)\\n- `AgentType` is the **display name** stored in metadata/trailers (title case: `\\\"Claude Code\\\"`)\\n- Both are defined as type aliases in `cmd/entire/cli/agent/types/agent.go`\\n- Constants are defined in `registry.go` alongside the default agent\\n- `DefaultAgentName` is set to `AgentNameClaudeCode`\\n\\n### 2. **Agent Implementation Structure**\\n\\nEach agent lives in its own subdirectory: `cmd/entire/cli/agent/{agentname}/`\\n\\nExisting agents:\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode/`\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/`\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/geminicli/`\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/opencode/`\\n\\n**File organization (pattern used by all agents):**\\n```\\nagentname/\\n├── agentname.go           # Core Agent interface + init() registration\\n├── lifecycle.go           # ParseHookEvent implementation + HookNames\\n├── types.go               # Hook input structs, transcript types\\n├── hooks.go               # HookSupport implementation (if applicable)\\n├── transcript.go          # TranscriptAnalyzer implementation (if applicable)\\n├── lifecycle_test.go      # Tests for ParseHookEvent\\n├── hooks_test.go          # Tests for hook installation\\n└── transcript_test.go     # Tests for transcript analysis\\n```\\n\\n### 3. **Core Agent Interface Methods**\\n\\nEvery agent must implement all 19 methods on the `Agent` interface:\\n\\n**Identity (5 methods):**\\n- `Name() types.AgentName` - Registry key (e.g., `\\\"claude-code\\\"`)\\n- `Type() types.AgentType` - Display name (e.g., `\\\"Claude Code\\\"`)\\n- `Description() string` - Human-readable description for UI\\n- `DetectPresence(ctx context.Context) (bool, error)` - Check if agent is configured\\n- `ProtectedDirs() []string` - Directories to preserve during rewind (e.g., `[\\\".claude\\\"]`)\\n\\n**Event Mapping (2 methods):**\\n- `HookNames() []string` - Hook verbs that become CLI subcommands\\n- `ParseHookEvent(ctx context.Context, hookName string, stdin io.Reader) (*Event, error)` - **Core contribution surface** - translate native hooks to Events\\n\\n**Transcript Storage (3 methods):**\\n- `ReadTranscript(sessionRef string) ([]byte, error)` - Read raw transcript bytes\\n- `ChunkTranscript(ctx context.Context, content []byte, maxSize int) ([][]byte, error)` - Split large transcripts\\n- `ReassembleTranscript(chunks [][]byte) ([]byte, error)` - Recombine chunks\\n\\n**Session Management (9 methods):**\\n- `GetSessionID(input *HookInput) string` - Extract session ID from hook input\\n- `GetSessionDir(repoPath string) (string, error)` - Where agent stores session data\\n- `ResolveSessionFile(