\\", or \\\"startup\\\"), and initialPrompt.\\n\\nThe sessionEnd hook is executed when the agent session completes or is terminated, and can be used to cleanup temporary resources, generate session reports, or send notifications.\\n\\n## Configuration Format\\n\\nHook configurations are placed in .github/hooks/<hook-name>.json and use a format with version 1, containing hook objects with type \\\"command\\\" and bash or powershell commands.\\n\\n## Extending Behavior with Hooks\\n\\nHooks extend behavior at key lifecycle points, with preToolUse hooks able to deny or modify tool calls, and postToolUse hooks enabling custom post-processing.\\n\\nCopilot CLI provides a \\\"hook system\\\" that can execute external commands at specific points in a session (start, tool use, end).\\n\\n## Practical Use Cases\\n\\nHooks are custom scripts that run at specific points during a Copilot CLI session and can inspect prompts and tool calls, log information for auditing, and even block execution of certain commands.\\n\\n\\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks.\"}]},\"uuid\":\"bff99fc7-83cb-4b81-b7ef-5922496baef1\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-02T01:13:20.174Z\"},\"normalizedMessages\":[],\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"a380b634d2c4dfbaf\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01638cr2BVFvq7kC5BYM3NZt\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01YVXe4Pjsqg6LdHhSANNNGd\",\"uuid\":\"11af02f8-ee18-47a9-a172-915971710e96\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-02T01:13:20.176Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"11af02f8-ee18-47a9-a172-915971710e96\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/3\",\"sessionId\":\"2335990a-d6c5-4425-96b8-9c47a378a3bd\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/add-copilot-agent\",\"slug\":\"buzzing-tinkering-coral\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01AjfiWc3Rrp1DzLAaacuaX