\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"# GitHub Copilot Hooks Configuration Reference\\n\\n## Hook Types\\n\\nThe documentation describes six hook types that execute at different stages of agent sessions:\\n\\n1. **Session Start** - \\\"Executed when a new agent session begins or when resuming an existing session\\\"\\n2. **Session End** - \\\"Executed when the agent session completes or is terminated\\\"\\n3. **User Prompt Submitted** - \\\"Executed when the user submits a prompt to the agent\\\"\\n4. **Pre-Tool Use** - \\\"Executed before the agent uses any tool\\\" with permission to approve/deny\\n5. **Post-Tool Use** - \\\"Executed after a tool completes execution (whether successful or failed)\\\"\\n6. **Error Occurred** - \\\"Executed when an error occurs during agent execution\\\"\\n\\n## JSON Configuration Structure\\n\\nHooks are defined in a configuration file using this structure:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"version\\\": 1,\\n  \\\"hooks\\\": {\\n    \\\"sessionStart\\\": [],\\n    \\\"sessionEnd\\\": [],\\n    \\\"userPromptSubmitted\\\": [],\\n    \\\"preToolUse\\\": [],\\n    \\\"postToolUse\\\": [],\\n    \\\"errorOccurred\\\": []\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\nEach hook entry contains:\\n- `type`: \\\"command\\\"\\n- `bash` or `powershell`: Script path\\n- `cwd`: Working directory (optional)\\n- `timeoutSec`: Timeout in seconds (default 30)\\n- `comment`: Description (optional)\\n\\n## Input/Output Formats\\n\\n**Session Start Input:**\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"timestamp\\\": 1704614400000,\\n  \\\"cwd\\\": \\\"/path/to/project\\\",\\n  \\\"source\\\": \\\"new\\\",\\n  \\\"initialPrompt\\\": \\\"Create a new feature\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Pre-Tool Use** (most powerful hook):\\n- Input includes `toolName` and `toolArgs`\\n- Output can deny execution: `{\\\"permissionDecision\\\":\\\"deny\\\",\\\"permissionDecisionReason\\\":\\\"...\\\"}`\\n\\n**Post-Tool Use Input:**\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"timestamp\\\": 1704614700000,\\n  \\\"cwd\\\": \\\"/path/to/project\\\",\\n  \\\"toolName\\\": \\\"bash\\\",\\n  \\\"toolArgs\\\": \\\"{\\\\\\\"command\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"npm test\\\\\\\"}\\\",\\n  \\\"toolResult\\\": {\\n    \\\"resultType\\\": \\\"success\\\",\\n    \\\"textResultForLlm\\\": \\\"All tests passed\\\"\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## Key Example Use Cases\\n\\n- **Compliance auditing:** Log all actions across session lifecycle\\n- **Cost tracking:** Monitor tool usage per user\\n- **Security enforcement:** Block dangerous commands before execution\\n- **Integration:** Send alerts to Slack on failures\"}]},\"uuid\":\"baa6aff1-bb39-4e5b-89cc-f378a1bdaf28\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-02T01:16:13.050Z\"},\"normalizedMessages\":[],\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"a380b634d2c4dfbaf\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01638cr2BVFvq7kC5BYM3NZt\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01YVXe4Pjsqg6LdHhSANNNGd\",\"uuid\":\"71193037-2a0e-4724-80de-a64ac340cbd0\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-02T01:16:13.134Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"71193037-2a0e-4724-80de-a64ac340cbd0\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/3\",\"sessionId\":\"2335990a-d6c5-4425-96b8-9c47a378a3bd\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/add-copilot-agent\",\"slug\":\"buzzing-tinkering-coral\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01DwGgyTvz1DKVCrxUVX9aQs\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"# GitHub Copilot CLI Hooks: Complete Guide\\n\\n## Hook Types & Lifecycle Events\\n\\nThe documentation identifies six available hook triggers:\\n\\n1. **sessionStart** - Executes when a session begins\\n2. **sessionEnd** - Executes when a session concludes\\n3. **userPromptSubmitted** - Fires when the user provides input\\n4. **preToolUse** - Runs before the agent uses a tool\\n5. **postToolUse** - Runs after tool execution completes\\n6. **errorOccurred** - Triggers when an error happens during execution\\n\\n## Directory Structure\\n\\nHooks must be placed in `.github/hooks/` within your repository. The configuration file must reside on your repository's default branch for the coding agent, though the CLI loads hooks from the current working directory.\\n\\n## JSON Configuration Format\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"version\\\": 1,\\n  \\\"hooks\\\": {\\n    \\\"sessionStart\\\": [...],\\n    \\\"sessionEnd\\\": [...],\\n    \\\"userPromptSubmitted\\\": [...],\\n    \\\"preToolUse\\\": [...],\\n    \\\"postToolUse\\\": [...],\\n    \\\"errorOccurred\\\": [...]\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## Hook Command Structure\\n\\nEach hook supports this configuration:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"type\\\": \\\"command\\\",\\n  \\\"bash\\\": \\\"shell_command_here\\\",\\n  \\\"powershell\\\": \\\"powershell_command_here\\\",\\n  \\\"cwd\\\": \\\"working_directory\\\",\\n  \\\"timeoutSec\\\": 10,\\n  \\\"env\\\": {\\n    \\\"VARIABLE\\\": \\\"value\\\"\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## Key Configuration Details\\n\\n- **bash/powershell**: Separate shell-specific commands ensure cross-platform compatibility\\n- **cwd**: Specifies execution directory (default: \\\".\\\")\\n- **timeoutSec**: Default timeout is 30 seconds; adjust as needed for longer operations\\n- **env**: Custom environment variables passed to the script\\n\\n## Input/Output Format\\n\\nHooks receive JSON input via stdin containing execution context like timestamp, current working directory, and tool information. Output must be valid JSON on a single line. On Unix systems, use `jq -c` for validation; on Windows, employ `ConvertTo-Json -Compress`.\\n\\n## Practical Examples\\n\\n**Session logging**:\\n```json\\n\\\"sessionStart\\\": [\\n  {\\n    \\\"type\\\": \\\"command\\\",\\n    \\\"bash\\\": \\\"echo \\\\\\\"Session: $(date)\\\\\\\" >> logs/session.log\\\",\\n    \\\"powershell\\\": \\\"Add-Content logs/session.log \\\\\\\"Session: $(Get-Date)\\\\\\\"\\\",\\n    \\\"cwd\\\": \\\".\\\",\\n    \\\"timeoutSec\\\": 10\\n  }\\n]\\n```\\n\\n**External script execution**:\\n```json\\n\\\"userPromptSubmitted\\\": [\\n  {\\n    \\\"type\\\": \\\"command\\\",\\n    \\\"bash\\\": \\\"./scripts/log-prompt.sh\\\",\\n    \\\"powershell\\\": \\\"./scripts/log-prompt.ps1\\\",\\n    \\\"cwd\\\": \\\"scripts\\\",\\n    \\\"env\\\": {\\\"LOG_LEVEL\\\": \\\"INFO\\\"}\\n  }\\n]\\n```\\n\\n## Debugging Techniques\\n\\nEnable verbose logging with `set -x` in bash scripts to trace execution. Test hooks locally by piping sample JSON input and validating output structure with `jq`.\"}]},\"uuid\":\"4a730bdc-8a5e-4770-983e-4cbeb08eaf01\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-02T01:16:14.587Z\"},\"normalizedMessages\":[],\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"a380b634d2c4dfbaf\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01638cr2BVFvq7kC5BYM3NZt\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01YVXe4Pjsqg6LdHhSANNNGd\",\"uuid\":\"14313958-0e00-4c64-9912-a8439fdc3d7d\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-02T01:16:14.589Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"14313958-0e00-4c64-9912-a8439fdc3d7d\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/3\",\"sessionId\":\"2335990a-d6c5-4425-96b8-9c47a378a3bd\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/add-copilot-agent\",\"slug\":\"buzzing-tinkering-coral\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-02T01:16:18.172Z\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01LsEHvRUNwWbqLjMB9npWNU\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01E1EoiC96BuYncJXfdYgHML\",\"name\":\"WebFetch\",\"input\":{\"url\":\"https://docs.github.com/en/copilot/how-tos/set-up/install-copilot-cli\",\"prompt\":\"What is the exact binary name? How do you launch it? What are all the installation methods? What is the official product name? Is it \\\"copilot\\\" or \\\"github-copilot-cli\\\" or something else?\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":1806,\"ca