d as a core feature of all GitHub Copilot plans (Free, Pro, Pro+, Business, and Enterprise).\\n\\n\\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks.\"}]},\"uuid\":\"a8a84011-2cae-46bf-b9dd-b679afa5fc27\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-02T01:16:47.333Z\"},\"normalizedMessages\":[],\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"a380b634d2c4dfbaf\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01638cr2BVFvq7kC5BYM3NZt\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01YVXe4Pjsqg6LdHhSANNNGd\",\"uuid\":\"26a0f20a-792a-429e-ae62-62f111883f10\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-02T01:16:47.365Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"26a0f20a-792a-429e-ae62-62f111883f10\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/3\",\"sessionId\":\"2335990a-d6c5-4425-96b8-9c47a378a3bd\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/add-copilot-agent\",\"slug\":\"buzzing-tinkering-coral\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"PostToolUse\",\"hookName\":\"PostToolUse:Agent\",\"command\":\"go run ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks claude-code post-task\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01YVXe4Pjsqg6LdHhSANNNGd\",\"toolUseID\":\"toolu_01YVXe4Pjsqg6LdHhSANNNGd\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-02T01:17:14.818Z\",\"uuid\":\"d0cdac07-f310-4c60-b449-c6f569caa6f6\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"f9c2812e-fe79-475b-8206-2b0aa7110528\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/3\",\"sessionId\":\"2335990a-d6c5-4425-96b8-9c47a378a3bd\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/add-copilot-agent\",\"slug\":\"buzzing-tinkering-coral\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01YVXe4Pjsqg6LdHhSANNNGd\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Here are my complete findings:\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 1. Binary Name\\n\\nThe binary name is **`copilot`**. It is a standalone executable, not a `gh` extension.\\n\\n- npm package: `@github/copilot`\\n- Homebrew formula: `copilot-cli`\\n- After installation, the command is simply `copilot`\\n\\n**Important distinction:** There was an older, now-deprecated tool called `gh copilot` (the `gh-copilot` extension for GitHub CLI). That was deprecated on October 25, 2025 and replaced by this standalone `copilot` binary. The old one only had `gh copilot suggest` and `gh copilot explain`. The new one is a full agentic coding tool.\\n\\n## 2. Lifecycle Hooks -- YES, it supports them\\n\\nCopilot CLI has a full hook system with **six hook types**:\\n\\n| Hook Name | When it fires |\\n|---|---|\\n| `sessionStart` | When a new agent session begins or resumes |\\n| `sessionEnd` | When the agent session completes or is terminated |\\n| `userPromptSubmitted` | When the user submits a prompt to the agent |\\n| `preToolUse` | Before the agent uses any tool (can approve/deny) |\\n| `postToolUse` | After a tool completes execution |\\n| `errorOccurred` | When an error occurs during agent execution |\\n\\nHooks receive **JSON input via stdin** and produce **JSON output on stdout**. For example, `sessionStart` receives:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"timestamp\\\": 1704614400000,\\n  \\\"cwd\\\": \\\"/path/to/project\\\",\\n  \\\"source\\\": \\\"new\\\",\\n  \\\"initialPrompt\\\": \\\"Create a new feature\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThe `preToolUse` hook can deny tool execution by outputting:\\n```json\\n{\\\"permissionDecision\\\": \\\"deny\\\", \\\"permissionDecisionReason\\\": \\\"...\\\"}\\n```\\n\\n## 3. Official Name\\n\\n**GitHub Copilot CLI** (often shortened to \\\"Copilot CLI\\\" in docs).\\n\\nThe GitHub repo is [github/copilot-cli](https://github.com/github/copilot-cli).\\n\\n## 4. How It Is Launched\\n\\n```bash\\n# Start interactive session\\ncopilot\\n\\n# Start with a prompt\\ncopilot -i \\\"describe what this repo does\\\"\\n\\n# Non-interactive single prompt\\ncopilot -p \\\"fix the failing test\\\"\\n\\n# Resume most recent session\\ncopilot --continue\\n\\n# Resume specific session\\ncopilot --resume SESSION-ID\\n\\n# Autopilot mode (no approval prompts)\\ncopilot --autopilot\\n```\\n\\nInstallation methods:\\n- `npm install -g @github/copilot`\\n- `brew install copilot-cli`\\n- `winget install GitHub.Copilot`\\n- `curl -fsSL https://gh.io/copilot-install | bash`\\n\\nRequires Node.js 22+ for the npm install path.\\n\\n## 5. Configuration File Format\\n\\n**Hooks configuration:** JSON files in `.github/hooks/*.json` (auto-discovered by glob pattern). Example path: `.github/hooks/copilot-cli-policy.json`\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"version\\\": 1,\\n  \\\"hooks\\\": {\\n    \\\"sessionStart\\\": [\\n      {\\n        \\\"type\\\": \\\"command\\\",\\n        \\\"bash\\\": \\\"./scripts/session-banner.sh\\\",\\n        \\\"powershell\\\": \\\"./scripts/session-banner.ps1\\\",\\n        \\\"cwd\\\": \\\".\\\",\\n        \\\"timeoutSec\\\": 10,\\n        \\\"env\\\": {\\n          \\\"LOG_LEVEL\\\": \\\"INFO\\\"\\n        }\\n      }\\n    ],\\n    \\\"userPromptSubmitted\\\": [...],\\n    \\\"preToolUse\\\": [...],\\n    \\\"postToolUse\\\": [...],\\n    \\\"sessionEnd\\\": [...],\\n    \\\"errorOccurred\\\": [...]\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**LSP configuration:** `~/.copilot/lsp-config.json` (user-level) or `.github/lsp.json` (repo-level).\\n\\n**Custom instructions:** Created via `copilot init` command.\\n\\n## 6. Hook/Extension System Documentation\\n\\nThe hooks system is well-documented by GitHub:\\n\\n- Each hook entry has `type: \\\"command\\\"` with `bash` and/or `powershell` script fields\\n- Hooks support custom `cwd`, `timeoutSec` (default 30s), `env` variables, and a `comment` field\\n- All `*.json` files in `.github/hooks/` are auto-loaded\\n- `preToolUse` is the most powerful hook -- it can block tool execution\\n- Copilot CLI also supports MCP (Model Context Protocol) servers for extending capabilities, and ships with GitHub's MCP server by default\\n- Plugin management via `copilot plugin` subcommand\\n\\n---\\n\