                                        // scale per-test timeouts\\n    RunPrompt(ctx context.Context, dir string, prompt string, opts ...Option) (Output, error)\\n    StartSession(ctx context.Context, dir string) (Session, error)   // interactive mode\\n    Bootstrap() error                                                  // one-time CI setup\\n    IsTransientError(out Output, err error) bool                      // detect retry-able failures\\n}\\n\\ntype Session interface {\\n    Send(input string) error\\n    WaitFor(pattern string, timeout time.Duration) (string, error)\\n    Capture() string\\n    Close() error\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Key features:**\\n- Registration pattern: agents call `Register(&Agent{})` in `init()`\\n- Concurrency gating: `RegisterGate(name, maxConcurrent)` limits parallel test execution\\n- Transient error detection: `IsTransientError()` triggers scenario restart with fresh repo\\n- Output capture: `Output` struct contains `Command`, `Stdout`, `Stderr`, `ExitCode`\\n\\n### 2. **Claude Code Implementation** (`e2e/agents/claude.go`)\\n\\n**RunPrompt approach:**\\n- Creates clean `CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR` temp directory (isolated from user settings)\\n- Removes `CLAUDECODE` env var to allow testing\\n- Sets `ACCESSIBLE=1` and `ENTIRE_TEST_TTY=0` \\n- Uses `exec.CommandContext` with process group handling (`Setpgid: true`) for clean termination\\n- Captures stdout/stderr independently\\n- Disables non-essential traffic (marketplace, auto-updates)\\n\\n**StartSession approach (interactive):**\\n- Uses `NewTmuxSession` (see below)\\n- Dismisses 5 startup dialogs (confirming permissions, etc.) before ready\\n- Looks for `❯` prompt pattern\\n- Handles \\\"Yes, I accept\\\" dialogs by sending Down arrow first\\n\\n**Bootstrap:**\\n- On CI, writes `.claude.json` with API key from `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`\\n- Locally, writes minimal config to skip onboarding\\n- Idempotent\\n\\n**Transient error patterns:**\\n- `\\\"overloaded\\\"`, `\\\"rate limit\\\"`, `\\\"529\\\"`, `\\\"503\\\"`, `\\\"ECONNRESET\\\"`, `\\\"ETIMEDOUT\\\"`\\n\\n### 3. **Gemini Implementation** (`e2e/agents/gemini.go`)\\n\\n**Differences from Claude:**\\n- Default model: `gemini-2.5-flash` (vs haiku for Claude)\\n- Concurrency limit: 2 (registered with `RegisterGate(\\\"gemini-cli\\\", 2)`)\\n- TimeoutMultiplier: `2.5×` (slower agent)\\n- PromptPattern: `\\\"Type your message\\\"` (not `❯`)\\n- Per-prompt timeout: 60s (respects `E2E_TIMEOUT`)\\n- Unsets `CI` and `GITHUB_ACTIONS` env vars before interactive session (forces interactive TUI)\\n\\n**Bootstrap:**\\n- Pre-configures `~/.gemini/settings.json` with auth type selected\\n\\n**Transient patterns:**\\n- `\\\"INTERNAL\\\"`, `\\\"Incomplete JSON segment\\\"`, `\\\"429\\\"`, `\\\"TooManyRequests\\\"`, `\\\"RESOURCE_EXHAUSTED\\\"`, `\\\"UNAVAILABLE\\\"`, `\\\"DEADLINE_EXCEEDED\\\"`\\n- Also detects `context.DeadlineExceeded`\\n\\n### 4. **OpenCode Implementation** (`e2e/agents/opencode.go`)\\n\\n**Registration:**\\n- Checks `opencode` binary exists before registering\\n- Reads `E2E_OPENCODE_MODEL` env var (defaults to `anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5`)\\n\\n**Bootstrap:**\\n- Runs 3 warmup attempts with `opencode run \\\"say hi\\\"` (DB migration + node_modules)\\n- Non-fatal (doesn't block tests if warmup fails)\\n\\n**StartSession:**\\n- Retry logic: if first attempt produces empty pane, retries once\\n- WaitFor pattern: `\\\"Ask anything|▣\\\"`\\n\\n**Transient patterns:**\\n- Includes `\\\"Token refresh failed\\\"`, `\\\"database is locked\\\"`\\n\\n### 5. **TmuxSession Helper** (`e2e/agents/tmux.go`)\\n\\nInteractive session management using tmux as a PTY multiplexer:\\n\\n**NewTmuxSession:**\\n- Creates tmux session with `tmux new-session -d -s <name> -c <dir>`\\n- Shells out env vars via `env -u VAR` prefixes (shell-quoted for safety)\\n- Sets `remain-on-exit on` to keep pane alive after command exits\\n- Registers cleanup functions with `OnClose()`\\n\\n**Send(input):**\\n1. Snapshot pre-send state with `stableContent()`\\n2. Send text and Enter separately (Claude's TUI can swallow Enter)\\n3. Wait for echo by polling until content changes\\n4. Only return when echoed input appears (prevents false matches)\\n5. Stores snapshot in `stableAtSend` for WaitFor to compare against\\n\\n**WaitFor(pattern, timeout):**\\n1. Compiles regex, polls with 500ms interval\\n2. Detects content changes (ignores last 3 lines for status bar updates)\\n3. Waits for pattern match + 2-second content stability (prevents settling on echoed input)\\n4. Requires content to have changed at least once since Send (avoids false settle)\\n5. Returns full pane content on success, error with pane dump on timeout\\n\\n**stableContent():**\\n- Strips last 3 lines to ignore TUI status bar changes\\n- Allows pattern to settle even when status bar is updating\\n\\n### 6. **Test Utilities** (`e2e/testutil/repo.go`)\\n\\n**RepoState:**\\n- Holds per-test repo snapshot: agent, dir, artifact dir, console log\\n- Tracks `HeadBefore` and `CheckpointBefore` for assertions\\n- Registers cleanup and artifact capture\\n\\n**SetupRepo(agent):**\\n1. Creates temp dir with `os.MkdirTemp` (not `t.TempDir()` — nested structure confuses agents)\\n2. Symlinks away `/var` on macOS for consistent paths\\n3. Initializes git, sets user config, makes initial commit\\n4. Runs `entire enable --agent <agent>`\\n5. Sets log_level to \\\"debug\\\" in settings\\n6. Writes `opencode.json` config if needed\\n7. Captures HEAD and checkpoint branch states before test\\n\\n**ForEachAgent(timeout, fn):**\\n1. Runs test subtest per registered agent\\n2. Acquires concurrency slot before test (blocks if gate is full)\\n3. Scales timeout by agent's `TimeoutMultiplier()`\\n4. Implements scenario restart on transient API errors (up to 3 attempts)\\n5. Recovers from `errScenarioRestart` panic and restarts with fresh repo\\n6. Releases slot on completion\\n\\n**RunPrompt(ctx, prompt, opts):**\\n- Delegates to `s.Agent.RunPrompt()`\\n- Logs full command and output to `console.log`\\n- Detects transient errors via `IsTransientError()`\\n- Panics with `errScenarioRestart` to trigger repo refresh\\n- Preserves artifacts from final attempt, suppresses artifacts from restarts\\n\\n### 7. **Test Assertions** (`e2e/testutil/assertions.go`)\\n\\n**Polling helpers:**\\n- `WaitForCheckpoint()` — polls until checkpoint branch advances\\n- `WaitForCheckpointAdvanceFrom()` — polls until branch moves past a ref\\n- `WaitForSessionMetadata()` — polls until session metadata appears on checkpoint branch\\n- `WaitForSessionIdle()` — polls until session phase becomes idle\\n- `WaitForFileExists()` — polls for file glob pattern\\n\\n**Branch/Shadow assertions:**\\n- `AssertNoShadowBranches()` — shadow branches cleaned up after commit\\n- `AssertHasShadowBranches()` — shadow branches persisted (session idle)\\n- `AssertCheckpointAdvanced()` / `AssertCheckpointNotAdvanced()`\\n\\n**Checkpoint assertions:**\\n- `AssertCheckpointIDFormat()` — validates 12 lowercase hex chars\\n- `AssertHasCheckpointTrailer()` / `AssertNoCheckpointTrailer()` — commit links\\n- `AssertCheckpointExists()` — metadata exists on checkpoint branch\\n- `AssertCommitLinkedToCheckpoint()` — both trailer and metadata exist\\n- `AssertCheckpointFilesTouched()` — validates exact files list\\n\\n**Metadata reading:**\\n- `ReadCheckpointMetadata()` — reads checkpoint-level metadata\\n- `ReadSessionMetadata()` — reads session-level metadata (indexed by session number)\\n- `CheckpointIDs()` — lists all checkpoint IDs from tree\\n- `NewCheckpointCommits()` — lists new commits on checkpoint branch since setup\\n\\n**Deep validation:**\\n- `ValidateCheckpointDeep()` — comprehensive check: metadata, transcript JSONL, content hash, prompts\\n\\n### 8. **Entry Points**\\n\\n**e2e/entire/entire.go:**\\n- Wrapper around `entire` CLI binary\\n- `BinPath()` — reads `E2E_ENTIRE_BIN` env var\\n- `Enable()`, `Disable()`, `RewindList()`, `Rewind()`, `Explain()` — CLI operations\\n- `run()` — executes with `ENTIRE_TEST_TTY=0`\\n- Error type `ExecError` wraps command output\\n\\n**e2e/bootstrap/main.go:**\\n- Called before tests: `go run ./e2e/bootstrap`\\n- Iterates all registered agents, calls `Bootstrap()` for CI setup\\n\\n### 9. **Directory Structure**\\n\\n```\\ne2e/\\n├── agents/           # Agent implementations (claude.go, gemini.go, opencode.go)\\n├── entire/           # CLI wrapper\\n├── testutil/         # Repo setup, assertions, metadata reading\\n├── tests/            # Blessed test files (run by CI)\\n├── exploratory/      # Experimental tests (not in CI)\\n├── bootstrap/        # Pre-test setup\\n└── README.md         # Full documentation\\n```\\n\\n### 10. **Environment Variables**\\n\\n| Variable | Purpose | Default |\\n|----------|---------|---------|\\n| `E2E_AGENT` | Filter agents (e.g., `claude-code`, `gemini-cli`, `opencode`) | all registered |\\n| `E2E_ENTIRE_BIN` | Path to built `entire` binary | builds from source |\\n| `E2E_TIMEOUT` | Per-prompt timeout | `2m` |\\n| `E2E_KEEP_REPOS` | Preserve temp repos after test | unset (clean up) |\\n| `E2E_ARTIFACT_DIR` | Override artifact output dir | `e2e/artifacts/<timestamp>` |\\n| `E2E_CONCURRENT_TEST_LIMIT` | Override concurrency gate | agent-specific default |\\n| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | Required for Claude Code | — |\\n| `GEMINI_API_KEY` | Required for Gemini CLI | — |\\n| `E2E_OPENCODE_MODEL` | Model for OpenCode | `anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5` |\\n| `ACCESSIBLE=1` | Enable accessibility mode | (set by agents) |\\n| `ENTIRE_TEST_TTY=0` | Disable TTY (non-interactive) | (set by agents) |\\n| `CI` | CI environment indicator | (read by Claude bootstrap) |\\n\\nAll contents have been read in full and are ready for use.\"},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"agentId: a69128e2171f0e2b8 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\\n<usage>total_tokens: 78312\\ntool_uses: 10\\nduration_ms: 38416</usage>\"}]}]},\"uuid\":\"6ac15ca3-29af-4fb4-b53a-69dcf6e8a135\",\"timestamp