tent\":\"     1→# Copilot CLI — Integration One-Pager\\n     2→\\n     3→## Verdict: COMPATIBLE\\n     4→\\n     5→Copilot CLI has a complete hook system with 8 hook types, JSONL transcripts, and session management. All required lifecycle events map cleanly.\\n     6→\\n     7→## Static Checks\\n     8→\\n     9→| Check | Result | Notes |\\n    10→|-------|--------|-------|\\n    11→| Binary present | PASS | `/opt/homebrew/bin/copilot` |\\n    12→| Help available | PASS | Full `--help` with subcommands |\\n    13→| Version info | PASS | `0.0.420` |\\n    14→| Hook keywords | PASS | 8 hook types in `.github/hooks/*.json` |\\n    15→| Session keywords | PASS | `--resume`, `--continue`, `--share` |\\n    16→| Config directory | PASS | `~/.copilot/` (user-level), `.github/hooks/` (repo-level) |\\n    17→| Documentation | PASS | docs.github.com/en/copilot/reference/hooks-configuration |\\n    18→\\n    19→## Binary\\n    20→\\n    21→- Name: `copilot`\\n    22→- Version: `0.0.420` (GA as of 2026-02-25)\\n    23→- Install: `brew install copilot-cli` or `npm install -g @github/copilot`\\n    24→\\n    25→## Hook Mechanism\\n    26→\\n    27→- Config file: `.github/hooks/*.json` (all JSON files in directory are auto-discovered)\\n    28→- Our file: `.github/hooks/entire.json` (dedicated file, avoids conflicts)\\n    29→- Config format: JSON\\n    30→- Hook registration: Array of hook entries per event name, each with `type: \\\"command\\\"` and `bash` field\\n    31→\\n    32→### Hook Config Format\\n    33→\\n    34→```json\\n    35→{\\n    36→  \\\"version\\\": 1,\\n    37→  \\\"hooks\\\": {\\n    38→    \\\"hookName\\\": [\\n    39→      {\\n    40→        \\\"type\\\": \\\"command\\\",\\n    41→        \\\"bash\\\": \\\"entire hooks copilot-cli hook-name\\\"\\n    42→      }\\n    43→    ]\\n    44→  }\\n    45→}\\n    46→```\\n    47→\\n    48→Note: Uses `bash` key (not `command` like Claude Code/Gemini). Also supports `powershell` for Windows. Each entry can have optional `cwd`, `timeoutSec` (default 30), `env`, and `comment` fields.\\n    49→\\n    50→### Hook Names and Event Mapping\\n    51→\\n    52→| Native Hook Name | When It Fires | Stdin Payload Fields | Entire EventType |\\n    53→|-----------------|---------------|---------------------|-----------------|\\n    54→| `userPromptSubmitted` | User submits a prompt | `timestamp`, `cwd`, `sessionId`, `prompt` | `TurnStart` |\\n    55→| `sessionStart` | Agent session begins/resumes | `timestamp`, `cwd`, `sessionId`, `source`, `initialPrompt` | `SessionStart` |\\n    56→| `agentStop` | Agent finishes a turn | `timestamp`, `cwd`, `sessionId`, `transcriptPath`, `stopReason` | `TurnEnd` |\\n    57→| `sessionEnd` | Session completed/terminated | `timestamp`, `cwd`, `sessionId`, `reason` | `SessionEnd` |\\n    58→| `subagentStop` | Subagent finishes | `timestamp`, `cwd`, `sessionId`, *(TBD — needs capture)* | `SubagentEnd` |\\n    59→| `preToolUse` | Before tool execution | *(TBD — needs capture)* | *(pass-through)* |\\n    60→| `postToolUse` | After tool execution | *(TBD — needs capture)* | *(pass-through)* |\\n    61→| `errorOccurred` | Error during execution | *(TBD — needs capture)* | *(pass-through)* |\\n    62→\\n    63→**Event ordering quirk:** `userPromptSubmitted` fires BEFORE `sessionStart` on the first prompt. This matches Claude Code's behavior and the framework's session phase state machine handles it correctly (TurnStart can arrive before SessionStart).\\n    64→\\n    65→**Valid Entire EventTypes:** `SessionStart`, `TurnStart`, `TurnEnd`, `Compaction`, `SessionEnd`, `SubagentStart`, `SubagentEnd`\\n    66→\\n    67→### Hook Input Payloads (Captured)\\n    68→\\n    69→**userPromptSubmitted:**\\n    70→```json\\n    71→{\\\"timestamp\\\":1771480081360,\\\"cwd\\\":\\\"/path/to/repo\\\",\\\"sessionId\\\":\\\"b0ff98c0-8e01-4b73-bf92-9649b139931b\\\",\\\"prompt\\\":\\\"hi\\\"}\\n    72→```\\n    73→\\n    74→**sessionStart:**\\n    75→```json\\n    76→{\\\"timestamp\\\":1771480081383,\\\"cwd\\\":\\\"/path/to/repo\\\",\\\"sessionId\\\":\\\"b0ff98c0-8e01-4b73-bf92-9649b139931b\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"new\\\",\\\"initialPrompt\\\":\\\"hi\\\"}\\n    77→```\\n    78→\\n    79→**agentStop:**\\n    80→```json\\n    81→{\\\"timestamp\\\":1771480085412,\\\"cwd\\\":\\\"/path/to/repo\\\",\\\"sessionId\\\":\\\"b0ff98c0-8e01-4b73-bf92-9649b139931b\\\",\\\"transcriptPath\\\":\\\"/home/user/.copilot/session-state/b0ff98c0-8e01-4b73-bf92-9649b139931b/events.jsonl\\\",\\\"stopReason\\\":\\\"end_turn\\\"}\\n    82→```\\n    83→\\n    84→**sessionEnd:**\\n    85→```json\\n    86→{\\\"timestamp\\\":1771480085425,\\\"cwd\\\":\\\"/path/to/repo\\\",\\\"sessionId\\\":\\\"b0ff98c0-8e01-4b73-bf92-9649b139931b\\\",\\\"reason\\\":\\\"complete\\\"}\\n    87→```\\n    88→\\n    89→## Transcript\\n    90→\\n    91→- Location: `~/.copilot/session-state/<sessionId>/events.jsonl`\\n    92→- Format: JSONL (one JSON object per line)\\n    93→- Session ID extraction: `sessionId` field in hook payloads (UUID format)\\n    94→- Session ID format: UUID (`b0ff98c0-8e01-4b73-bf92-9649b139931b`)\\n    95→\\n    96→### Transcript Entry Schema\\n    97→\\n    98→Each line has: `type`, `data`, `id` (UUID), `timestamp` (ISO 8601), `parentId`\\n    99→\\n   100→**Event types observed:**\\n   101→- `session.start` — Session metadata (sessionId, version, producer, copilotVersion, context)\\n   102→- `user.message` — User messages (`content`, `transformedContent`, `attachments`, `interactionId`)\\n   103→- `assistant.turn_start` — Start of assistant turn (`turnId`, `interactionId`)\\n   104→- `assistant.message` — Assistant response (`content`, `toolRequests[]`, `reasoningText`)\\n   105→- `assistant.turn_end` — End of assistant turn (`turnId`)\\n   106→\\n   107→**Example entries:**\\n   108→```jsonl\\n   109→{\\\"type\\\":\\\"session.start\\\",\\\"data\\\":{\\\"sessionId\\\":\\\"4de47255-...\\\",\\\"version\\\":1,\\\"producer\\\":\\\"copilot-agent\\\",\\\"copilotVersion\\\":\\\"0.0.420\\\",\\\"startTime\\\":\\\"2026-03-02T01:11:45.379Z\\\",\\\"context\\\":{\\\"cwd\\\":\\\"/path\\\",\\\"gitRoot\\\":\\\"/path\\\",\\\"branch\\\":\\\"main\\\",\\\"repository\\\":\\\"org/repo\\\"}},\\\"id\\\":\\\"c1c1...\\\",\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"2026-03-02T01:11:45.421Z\\\",\\\"parentId\\\":null}\\n   110→{\\\"type\\\":\\\"user.message\\\",\\\"data\\\":{\\\"content\\\":\\\"exit\\\",\\\"transformedContent\\\":\\\"...\\\",\\\"attachments\\\":[],\\\"interactionId\\\":\\\"6cd0...\\\"},\\\"id\\\":\\\"20fa...\\\",\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"...\\\",\\\"parentId\\\":\\\"00ac...\\\"}\\n   111→{\\\"type\\\":\\\"assistant.turn_start\\\",\\\"data\\\":{\\\"turnId\\\":\\\"0\\\",\\\"interactionId\\\":\\\"6cd0...\\\"},\\\"id\\\":\\\"3b61...\\\",\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"...\\\",\\\"parentId\\\":\\\"20fa...\\\"}\\n   112→{\\\"type\\\":\\\"assistant.message\\\",\\\"data\\\":{\\\"messageId\\\":\\\"a078...\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"To exit...\\\",\\\"toolRequests\\\":[],\\\"interactionId\\\":\\\"6cd0...\\\",\\\"reasoningText\\\":\\\"...\\\"},\\\"id\\\":\\\"c892...\\\",\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"...\\\",\\\"parentId\\\":\\\"aaeb...\\\"}\\n   113→{\\\"type\\\":\\\"assistant.turn_end\\\",\\\"data\\\":{\\\"turnId\\\":\\\"0\\\"},\\\"id\\\":\\\"0ae4...\\\",\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"...\\\",\\\"parentId\\\":\\\"4989...\\\"}\\n   114→```\\n   115→\\n   116→### Tool Usage in Transcripts\\n   117→\\n   118→The `assistant.message` entries have a `toolRequests` array. When the agent uses tools (edit_file, write_file, shell, etc.), these will contain tool call details. Exact schema TBD — needs a session with actual tool usage.\\n   119→\\n   120→### Transcript Position\\n   121→\\n   122→Position = line count (JSONL format). Use `agent.ChunkJSONL()` / `agent.ReassembleJSONL()` for chunking.\\n   123→\\n   124→## Session State Directory\\n   125→\\n   126→```\\n   127→~/.copilot/session-state/<sessionId>/\\n   128→├── events.jsonl          # Transcript (JSONL)\\n   129→├── workspace.yaml        # Workspace metadata (cwd, git info, summary)\\n   130→├── checkpoints/          # Agent's own checkpoints\\n   131→├── files/                # File snapshots\\n   132→├── research/             # Research data\\n   133→└── rewind-snapshots/     # Agent's rewind snapshots\\n   134→```\\n   135→\\n   136→## Config Preservation\\n   137→\\n   138→- Hook config is in `.github/hooks/*.json` — each file is auto-discovered\\n   139→- We create a **dedicated** `.github/hooks/entire.json` file, leaving other hook files untouched\\n   140→- No need for read-modify-write of existing files\\n   141→- If `entire.json` already exists, read-modify-write to preserve any user additions\\n   142→\\n   143→## CLI Flags\\n   144→\\n   145→- Non-interactive prompt: `copilot -p \\\"prompt\\\" --allow-all-tools`\\n   146→- Interactive with initial prompt: `copilot -i \\\"prompt\\\"`\\n   147→- Interactive mode: `copilot`\\n   148→- Resume most recent: `copilot --continue`\\n   149→- Resume specific: `copilot --resume <sessionId>`\\n   150→- Autopilot (no confirmations): `copilot --autopilot`\\n   151→- Config directory: `--config-dir <dir>` (default: `~/.copilot`)\\n   152→- Relevant env vars: `COPILOT_ALLOW_ALL` (equivalent to `--allow-all-tools`)\\n   153→\\n   154→## Presence Detection\\n   155→\\n   156→- No repo-level `.copilot/` directory (unlike other agents)\\n   157→- Check for `.github/hooks/entire.json` containing copilot-cli hooks\\n   158→- Alternative: check for `copilot` binary in PATH\\n   159→\\n   160→## Protected Directories\\n   161→\\n   162→- `.github` — contains hook configs (committed to repo, unlikely to be affected by rewind)\\n   163→- No agent-specific repo directory to protect\\n   164→\\n   165→## Gaps & Limitations\\n   166→\\n   167→- `subagentStop` payload not yet captured (need a session that spawns subagents)\\n   168→- `preToolUse` / `postToolUse` payloads not yet captured (need a session with tool usage)\\n   169→- No `Compaction` event — Copilot CLI doesn't appear to have a context compaction hook\\n   170→- No `SubagentStart` event — only `subagentStop` is available (one-sided)\\n   171→- Tool request schema in transcripts needs verification with a real tool-using session\\n   172→- `transcriptPath` only available in `agentStop` hook — `userPromptSubmitted` and `sessionStart` don't include it, so we compute it from `~/.copilot/session-state/<sessionId>/events.jsonl`\\n   173→\\n   174→## Captured Payloads\\n   175→\\n   176→- Hook capture logs: `tmp/test-copilot/logs/copilot-hooks.jsonl`\\n   177→- Local transcript: `~/.copilot/session-state/4de47255-3d43-4938-b8fa-b6e49f1d0aca/events.jsonl`\\n   178→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"9994e4e9-b4b8-44a5-9e1c-8e56951d9f78\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-02T01:47:51.588Z\"},\"normalizedMessages\":[],\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"aacfebfd90f1c2e60\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01QVxAUDELRC3crvorhsbcKF\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01GwXaK2TNEcWCuXAdU2zhY9\",\"uuid\":\"58474188-cdce-46a4-be2b-ce30c77c0ea5\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-02T01:47:51.590Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"58474188-cdce-46a4-be2b-ce30c77c0ea5\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/3\",\"sessionId\":\"2335990a-d6c5-4425-96b8-9c47a378a3bd\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/add-copilot-agent\",\"slug\":\"buzzing-tinkering-coral\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-02T01:47:54.949Z\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_012BeAf6wej4BP9EBQV6UiRj\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01N9Yd7r29RRGQpQLtZm44SE\",\"name\":\"Bash\",\"input\":{\"command\":\"ls /Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/3/cmd/entire/cli/agent/cursor/\",\"description\":\"List cursor agent files\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":3357,\"cache_read_i